article.headline: Southern Utah 97, UMKC 63
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Rand Janes scored 23 points and Southern Utah shot 63 percent in a 97-63 victory over Missouri-Kansas City Monday night. Janes went 7-9 from 3-point range, leading the Thunderbirds (2-11, 1-0 Mid-Continent Conference) to a 52-percent shooting performance behind the bonus line. Lubor Olsovsky scored a career-high 19 points for Southern Utah. Justin Allen had 13 points, Henry Uhegwu scored 12 and Fernando Bonfim added 10. Southern Utah finished with 24 assists, a season-high, on 32 baskets. Quinton Day scored 26 points for UMKC (4-7, 1-1). Brent Stephens had 11 points for the Kangaroos, and Kalu Guasco added 10, all in the first half. The Thunderbirds went 18-of-28 from the field and 7-of-15 from 3-point range in the first half. The Kangaroos missed their first nine shots and committed 11 first-half turnovers. Their first field goal, a layup by Day at 14:14, narrowed the Thunderbird lead to 15-4. Southern Utah led 51-27 at the half and stretched the lead to 35 points twice in the second half.
